<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-1128 </DOCNO><TEXT>A method of forming a flue lining within a structure including the stepsof defining a flue wall by disposing a rigid combustible former havinga uniform external surface in the structure such that a void extendsbetween the structure and the uniform external surface of the former;and filling the void with a hardenable non-combustible material whilein a flowable state and allowing the material to harden.</TEXT></DOC>